Key Match Events: The Houston Rockets outlasted the New York Knicks in a 109-97 win at home.
Alperen Sengun put up 25 points and 14 rebounds on 11-of-15 shooting, along with four blocks.
Fred VanVleet had a bounceback game with 19 points, five assists, two steals, and one block on 8-of-14 shooting.
The Rockets outscored the Knicks 20-19 in the third quarter and 28-22 in the fourth quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: Houston's stars showing out in the win is a great sign for the team.
The Rockets, now 4-3, will try to make this a winning streak as they face the San Antonio Spurs for the third time tomorrow.
